# Bank Management System

## Project Overview

The Bank Management System is a web-based application developed using Python, Flask, and MySQL. The system provides a secure and efficient way to manage banking operations such as customer registration, account creation, deposits, withdrawals, balance inquiries, and account management.

The project aims to automate traditional banking processes by storing customer and transaction data in a MySQL database and providing an easy-to-use interface through Flask. It demonstrates the integration of backend development, database management, and web application design.

## Features

* Customer Registration and Login
* Create New Bank Accounts
* Deposit Money
* Withdraw Money
* Check Account Balance
* View Customer Details
* Update Customer Information
* Delete Account Records
* Secure Database Connectivity using MySQL
* User-Friendly Web Interface with Flask

## Technologies Used

* Python
* Flask
* MySQL
* HTML
* CSS
* Jinja2 Templates

## Database

The project uses MySQL for data storage and management. Customer information, account details, and transaction records are securely maintained in relational database tables.

## Learning Outcomes

Through this project, I gained hands-on experience in:

* Web development using Flask
* Database connectivity with MySQL
* CRUD operations (Create, Read, Update, Delete)
* Backend application development
* Database design and management
* Building real-world software projects

## Future Enhancements

* Online fund transfer functionality
* Transaction history and statements
* Password encryption and authentication
* Email and SMS notifications
* Admin dashboard and reporting system
* Role-based access control

## Conclusion

This Bank Management System project demonstrates the practical implementation of Python Flask and MySQL to develop a real-world banking application. It serves as a strong foundation for learning full-stack development and database-driven web applications.
